This paper deals with a caching system that involves communication between a server and multiple users, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories. The paper also discusses the optimization of the system, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of bounds and tradeoffs, which could suggest the Learning (cs.LG) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories.
